      "@larkost On a side note, one of the modifications to the driver was to add logging to the `rawSocket.on('close')` event in `net.js`. The interesting this is I barely see these console.log lines being executed during normal operation of our application. When I do get logs, `port` is always undefined. The rest of the time we never reach the __on close__ handler. Any thoughts?\r\n\r\nHere is the modified code:\r\n\r\n```\r\nthis.rawSocket.on('close', (function(_this) {\r\n        return function() {\r\n          var port = _this.rawSocket.localPort;\r\n          console.log('Close connection');\r\n          console.log(port);\r\n          if (connections[port] !== undefined) {\r\n            delete connections[port];\r\n          }\r\n          console.log('^^ Close connection');\r\n          if (_this.isOpen()) {\r\n            _this.close({\r\n              noreplyWait: false\r\n            });\r\n          }\r\n          return _this.emit('close');\r\n        };\r\n      })(this));\r\n```"
